1 (a) Making the report; and
2 (b) Participating in any judicial proceeding that resulted from the report.
3 (10) Notice required pursuant to this section shall be given to:[ ]
4 (a) Any law enforcement agency created by the local board of education;[, and
5 to:]
6 (b)[(a)] A local law enforcement agency not created by the local board of
7 education; or
8 (c)[(b)] The Department of Kentucky State Police.
9 (11) (a) A local board of education that has created a law enforcement agency shall
10 designate a local law enforcement agency not created by the local board of
11 education to receive reporting information from the law enforcement
12 agency created by the local board of education.
13 (b) A law enforcement agency created by the local board of education shall file
14 a report each week with the local law enforcement agency designated
15 pursuant to paragraph (a) of this subsection identifying all reports received
16 pursuant to this section by the law enforcement agency created by the local
17 board of education during the preceding week.[
18 (11) Any person who intentionally violates the provisions of this section shall be guilty
19 of a:
20 (a) Class B misdemeanor for the first offense;
21 (b) Class A misdemeanor for the second offense; and
22 (c) Class D felony for the third or subsequent offense.]
23 Section 3. KRS 158.990 is amended to read as follows:
24 (1) Any member of a school board who votes to permit entrance to a school of any
25 child not eligible therefor under the provisions of KRS 158.030 shall be fined not
26 less than five dollars ($5) nor more than fifty dollars ($50).
27 (2) Any person who intentionally violates Section 2 of this Act shall be guilty of a:
Page 13 of 14
SB010120.100 - 1128 - XXXX 3/26/2026 2:33 PM Engrossed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 101/EN
1 (a) Class B misdemeanor for the first offense; and
2 (b) Class A misdemeanor for the second or subsequent offense[required to
3 report under KRS 158.155 who fails to report promptly or who refuses to
4 make a report is guilty of a Class A misdemeanor].
5 Section 4. KRS 159.170 is amended to read as follows:
6 (1) Whenever any child of compulsory school age withdraws from school, the teacher
7 of the student[child] shall ascertain the reason. The fact of the withdrawal and the
8 reason for it shall be immediately transmitted by the teacher to the superintendent
9 of schools of the district in which the school is located. If the student[child] has
10 withdrawn because of change of residence, the next residence shall be ascertained
11 and included in the report.
12 (2) The Kentucky Department of Education shall ensure that the student information
13 system facilitates the collection of student data and the transfer of education records
14 among schools and local districts.
15 (3) Within five (5) days of a student being expelled under Section 1 of this Act, a
16 school district shall enter the expulsion in the student's record within the student
17 information system.
18 (4) A school district shall notify the Kentucky Department of Education when a new
19 student enrolls in a school in the district.
20 (5)[(4)] The Kentucky Department of Education, upon notification of a student's
21 enrollment in a school, shall forward within ten (10) working days all records
22 regarding the student collected under this section to the receiving district.
